Romelu Lukaku has been fined along with three Inter Milan teammates after a party in the early hours of Thursday morning to celebrate the Belgium forward’s birthday which broke Covid-19 restrictions. Lukaku, Achraf Hakimi, Ivan Perisic and Ashley Young were among a group of 24 people celebrating his 28th birthday in a Milan hotel after Inter’s 3-1 league win over Roma, Gazzetta Dello Sport reported. Police were called with all present receiving fines for breaking coronavirus rules, Gazzetta said. According to Lukaku’s entourage, the former Manchester United forward went out with friends, but had not organised the party.